LORE – developed by AustLit for annotation, federated searching,
    visualization, aggregation and sharing of compound digital objects
    (Gerber, Hyland & Hunter 2010);

OHRMwww.esrc.unimelb.edu.au/ohrm/ – developed by the University of Melbourne
    to model entity relationships and publish information about collections
    into aggregated frameworks;

Tools for
                    extracting, exposing and transforming entity data contained in existing cultural
                    data sets and in digital objects;
